  "title": "The Articles of Confederation | Period 3: 1754-1800 | AP US History | Khan Academy",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 2954.0,
      "text": "- [Instructor] Hey, this is Kim and I&#39;m here with Leah,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2954.0,
      "end_time": 6150.0,
      "text": "Khan Academy&#39;s US Government and Politics Fellow."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 6150.0,
      "end_time": 6848.0,
      "text": "Welcome Leah."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 6848.0,
      "end_time": 7681.0,
      "text": "- [Leah] How&#39;s it going?"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 7681.0,
      "end_time": 8986.0,
      "text": "- [Kim] Alright, so we&#39;re talking about"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 8986.0,
      "end_time": 10816.0,
      "text": "the Articles of Confederation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 10816.0,
      "end_time": 12647.0,
      "text": "which I think many people don&#39;t realize"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 12647.0,
      "end_time": 15218.0,
      "text": "was the first constitution of the United States"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 15218.0,
      "end_time": 19192.0,
      "text": "before the one that we have now since 1789."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 19192.0,
      "end_time": 21760.0,
      "text": "So could you take us through a little bit"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 21760.0,
      "end_time": 23539.0,
      "text": "what the Articles of Confederation were"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 23539.0,
      "end_time": 26818.0,
      "text": "and the context in which we first brought them on"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 26818.0,
      "end_time": 28142.0,
      "text": "as a governmental system?"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 28142.0,
      "end_time": 30166.0,
      "text": "- [Leah] Sure, so I think the most important thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 30167.0,
      "end_time": 31818.0,
      "text": "to understand about the Articles of Confederation"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 31818.0,
      "end_time": 33821.0,
      "text": "and why we would talk about this"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 33821.0,
      "end_time": 36882.0,
      "text": "is because one of the biggest debates that we have"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 36883.0,
      "end_time": 39980.0,
      "text": "in our history is about the balance of power"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 39980.0,
      "end_time": 42484.0,
      "text": "between the federal government and state governments."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 42484.0,
      "end_time": 45274.0,
      "text": "When the Articles of Confederation were first created,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 45274.0,
      "end_time": 47290.0,
      "text": "it was in the middle of the American Revolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 47290.0,
      "end_time": 52107.0,
      "text": "They were created in 1777, and so the question becomes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 52107.0,
      "end_time": 53896.0,
      "text": "well, how can we run a government"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 53896.0,
      "end_time": 56703.0,
      "text": "that looks as different from monarchy as possible?"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 56703.0,
      "end_time": 59781.0,
      "text": "- [Kim] Right, so they&#39;re trying to run away from the past"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 59781.0,
      "end_time": 62324.0,
      "text": "that they&#39;re getting away from in the Revolutionary War"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 62325.0,
      "end_time": 65265.0,
      "text": "and trying to create a separate government"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 65265.0,
      "end_time": 67769.0,
      "text": "that doesn&#39;t have any of those abuses"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 67769.0,
      "end_time": 70124.0,
      "text": "that they are rebelling against."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 70124.0,
      "end_time": 71500.0,
      "text": "- [Leah] If they&#39;re running away from a monarchy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 71500.0,
      "end_time": 72486.0,
      "text": "what they&#39;re running towards"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 72486.0,
      "end_time": 74466.0,
      "text": "is what we would call limited government."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 74466.0,
      "end_time": 75298.0,
      "text": "- [Kim] OK."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 75299.0,
      "end_time": 76291.0,
      "text": "- [Leah] So their central government,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 76291.0,
      "end_time": 78878.0,
      "text": "which is synonymous with a federal government,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 78878.0,
      "end_time": 80650.0,
      "text": "the central government is actually"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 80650.0,
      "end_time": 82400.0,
      "text": "really, really, really small."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 82400.0,
      "end_time": 83233.0,
      "text": "- [Kim] OK."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 83233.0,
      "end_time": 84396.0,
      "text": "- [Leah] They don&#39;t have an executive branch."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 84396.0,
      "end_time": 85731.0,
      "text": "They only have Congress."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 85731.0,
      "end_time": 87669.0,
      "text": "They don&#39;t even have a judicial branch."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 87670.0,
      "end_time": 91295.0,
      "text": "So Congress is made up of all 13 states."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 91295.0,
      "end_time": 93327.0,
      "text": "Every state had one representative."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 93327.0,
      "end_time": 94160.0,
      "text": "- [Kim] OK."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 94160.0,
      "end_time": 96959.0,
      "text": "- [Leah] In order to change the Articles of Confederation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 96959.0,
      "end_time": 98759.0,
      "text": "if they wanted to pass an amendment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 98759.0,
      "end_time": 102598.0,
      "text": "they had to get unanimous consent from all 13 states."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 102598.0,
      "end_time": 104319.0,
      "text": "- [Kim] OK, so they&#39;re trying to make sure"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 104319.0,
      "end_time": 108642.0,
      "text": "that all of the states are represented equally,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 108642.0,
      "end_time": 112292.0,
      "text": "but that also sounds like it would have a lot of hurdles"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 112293.0,
      "end_time": 116408.0,
      "text": "to overcome when it comes to getting consensus."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 116408.0,
      "end_time": 118638.0,
      "text": "- [Leah] Yeah, for laws, you had to get nine"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 118638.0,
      "end_time": 121737.0,
      "text": "out of 13 states to actually pass a law."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 121737.0,
      "end_time": 124893.0,
      "text": "So if you can imagine, if you&#39;re in a room of 13 people"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 124893.0,
      "end_time": 127997.0,
      "text": "and you all have to agree on one pizza topping"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 127997.0,
      "end_time": 130169.0,
      "text": "for the rest of your lives. (Kim laughs)"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 130169.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131928.0,
      "text": "It would be almost impossible, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 131928.0,
      "end_time": 134819.0,
      "text": "- [Kim] Wow, OK, alright, so it sounds like"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 134819.0,
      "end_time": 138197.0,
      "text": "there are some problems with the Articles of Confederation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 138198.0,
      "end_time": 141501.0,
      "text": "but did they do anything good for us in this early period?"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 141501.0,
      "end_time": 142870.0,
      "text": "- [Leah] Yeah, so the biggest thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 142870.0,
      "end_time": 146652.0,
      "text": "is that it unites all 13 colonies who are now states"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 146652.0,
      "end_time": 148934.0,
      "text": "under one government."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 148934.0,
      "end_time": 149767.0,
      "text": "- [Kim] OK."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 149767.0,
      "end_time": 151158.0,
      "text": "- [Leah] This government is able to pass"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 151158.0,
      "end_time": 153744.0,
      "text": "a really favorable treaty with Britain"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 153745.0,
      "end_time": 157968.0,
      "text": "and end the Revolutionary War in 1783, the Treaty of Paris."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 157968.0,
      "end_time": 159804.0,
      "text": "- [Kim] OK, so this is kind of the government"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 159804.0,
      "end_time": 162110.0,
      "text": "that gets us through the revolutionary war"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 162110.0,
      "end_time": 166856.0,
      "text": "and is with us when we first start in the 1780s."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 166856.0,
      "end_time": 170110.0,
      "text": "- [Leah] Yeah, and one another specific law that they pass"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 170110.0,
      "end_time": 173224.0,
      "text": "is the Northwest Ordinance of 1787"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 173224.0,
      "end_time": 176226.0,
      "text": "and this Northwest Ordinance kinda tells us"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 176226.0,
      "end_time": 179413.0,
      "text": "how we are going to expand as we move west"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 179413.0,
      "end_time": 181470.0,
      "text": "and what are we going to do with that land,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 181470.0,
      "end_time": 183119.0,
      "text": "and that&#39;s a really important idea"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 183119.0,
      "end_time": 185978.0,
      "text": "when we&#39;re moving forward with our country."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 185978.0,
      "end_time": 188571.0,
      "text": "The only problem is with the Articles of Confederation"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 188571.0,
      "end_time": 191347.0,
      "text": "is there is a lot of things that we still have to figure out"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 191347.0,
      "end_time": 193535.0,
      "text": "as we&#39;re growing, there&#39;s a lot of growing pains."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 193535.0,
      "end_time": 196126.0,
      "text": "- [Kim] So what led the early government"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 196126.0,
      "end_time": 198850.0,
      "text": "of the United States to realize"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 198850.0,
      "end_time": 200873.0,
      "text": "that they wanted to abandon these Articles of Confederation"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 200873.0,
      "end_time": 203569.0,
      "text": "in favor of a different constitution?"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 203569.0,
      "end_time": 206214.0,
      "text": "- [Leah] So the inciting incident is Shays&#39; Rebellion."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 206214.0,
      "end_time": 209600.0,
      "text": "It happens in Massachusets, and it&#39;s a group of farmers"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 209600.0,
      "end_time": 211492.0,
      "text": "led by this guy named Daniel Shays."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 211492.0,
      "end_time": 213879.0,
      "text": "What&#39;s happening is that we had just gotten out of"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 213879.0,
      "end_time": 215861.0,
      "text": "the Revolutionary War, and a lot of of the people"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 215861.0,
      "end_time": 217410.0,
      "text": "who had fought in the Revolutionary War"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 217410.0,
      "end_time": 220490.0,
      "text": "still hadn&#39;t gotten payment for their duty."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 220500.0,
      "end_time": 223376.0,
      "text": "They also were experiencing really high state taxes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 223376.0,
      "end_time": 227638.0,
      "text": "so Daniel Shays and these farmers are very upset, obviously,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 227638.0,
      "end_time": 230874.0,
      "text": "in their wanting their money and so they started rebelling,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 230874.0,
      "end_time": 233447.0,
      "text": "but the problem is, with the way that the central government"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 233447.0,
      "end_time": 237147.0,
      "text": "that was built, first, Congress had no ability"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 237147.0,
      "end_time": 239388.0,
      "text": "to levy or collect taxes."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 239389.0,
      "end_time": 240607.0,
      "text": "If they couldn&#39;t collect taxes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 240607.0,
      "end_time": 244547.0,
      "text": "they had no ability to actually pay back their farmers."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 244547.0,
      "end_time": 247413.0,
      "text": "Along with that, they didn&#39;t have any money"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 247413.0,
      "end_time": 250648.0,
      "text": "to create a military, so each state had their own militia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 250648.0,
      "end_time": 253478.0,
      "text": "but the United States as a whole as a country"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 253478.0,
      "end_time": 256123.0,
      "text": "did not have a military to suppress this rebellion."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 256123.0,
      "end_time": 258457.0,
      "text": "So on both ends, we are in"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 258457.0,
      "end_time": 261690.0,
      "text": "a really bad situation politically."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 261690.0,
      "end_time": 263843.0,
      "text": "- [Kim] Wow, so, there&#39;s this moment"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 263843.0,
      "end_time": 267758.0,
      "text": "where you find armed rebellion against the United States"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 267758.0,
      "end_time": 271195.0,
      "text": "for a lack of money and the US government"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 271195.0,
      "end_time": 272957.0,
      "text": "finds that it can&#39;t raise money"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 272957.0,
      "end_time": 275907.0,
      "text": "and it can&#39;t raise an army to put down this rebellion."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 275907.0,
      "end_time": 279393.0,
      "text": "- [Leah] Exactly, and so there is this fear immediately."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 279393.0,
      "end_time": 281304.0,
      "text": "And what we see is a lot of the founding fathers"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 281305.0,
      "end_time": 284440.0,
      "text": "that we know and really respect today like George Washington"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 284440.0,
      "end_time": 287176.0,
      "text": "and Ben Franklin and Alexander Hamilton and James Madison,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 287177.0,
      "end_time": 289678.0,
      "text": "they get together and they say this is a problem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 289678.0,
      "end_time": 291685.0,
      "text": "we need to change what we have,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 291685.0,
      "end_time": 293728.0,
      "text": "and this leads to the Constitutional Convention"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 293728.0,
      "end_time": 296239.0,
      "text": "in which we draft our second constitution."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 296239.0,
      "end_time": 298964.0,
      "text": "- [Kim] Right, yeah, so in 1787,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 298964.0,
      "end_time": 302301.0,
      "text": "the leaders of the United States get together and say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 302301.0,
      "end_time": 304676.0,
      "text": "alright, the Articles of Confederation aren&#39;t working."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 304676.0,
      "end_time": 306884.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re gonna need a stronger central government,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 306884.0,
      "end_time": 309500.0,
      "text": "even though we were trying to get away from the monarchy"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 309500.0,
      "end_time": 311447.0,
      "text": "and now let&#39;s think of something"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 311447.0,
      "end_time": 313628.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s going to work a little bit better for us."
    }
  ]
}